                  {
                     "text": "#### Reforms\n\nAfter the unification of the northern kingdoms, there was a centralization and improvement of the central administration through a unified and simplified legal system. Furthermore, anti-corruption measures were adopted, with officials having a limited term of three or four years and being unable to govern in the region where they were born (<htcite0>).\n\nTo assist poorer farmers, the Equal Field System (*juntian* 均田) was reinforced, ensuring that small farmers would not lose their land to large landowners (<htcite1>; <htcite2>).\n\nThese legal system reforms perpetuated themselves, creating an entire legal foundation for China (Zhongguo 中國), which leads us to a new reflection:",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 1,
                           "uuid": "cd42262b-9421-4c44-b273-25caea45bfa8",
                           "text": "Cartwright, M.",
                           "page": "Sui Dynasty",
                           "date_time": {
                              "type": "gregory",
                              "year": "2017",
                              "month": "09",
                              "day": "22"
                           }
                        },
                        {
                           "type": 1,
                           "uuid": "cd42262b-9421-4c44-b273-25caea45bfa8",
                           "text": "Cartwright, M.",
                           "page": "Sui Dynasty",
                           "date_time": {
